.
"It is better to imitate ancient than modern work." — Leonardo da Vinci. #architectureoskar
.
#roma #rome #italy #leonardodavinci

node.text:
L'Arc de Triomphe, Wrapped. #archoskar
Designed by Jean Chalgrin & Louis-Étienne Héricart de Thury (1806).
Artwork by Christo and Jeanne-Claude (@christojeanneclaude, 2021).
Located in Place Charles de Gaulle, Paris, France.
Photos by Hans Ulrich Obrist (@hansulrichobrist).
Description by Christo and Jeanne-Claude.
.
"Art is the triumph over chaos." — John Cheever. #architectureoskar
.
L'Arc de Triomphe, Wrapped, a temporary artwork for Paris, is on view for 16 days from Saturday, September 18 to Sunday, October 3, 2021. The project has been realized in partnership with the Centre des Monuments Nationaux and in coordination with the City of Paris. It also receives the support of the Centre Pompidou. The Arc de Triomphe is wrapped in 25,000 square meters of recyclable polypropylene fabric in silvery blue, and with 3,000 meters of red rope.
.
#arcdetriomphe #wrap #paris #france

node.text:
Pick your favourite Patio 😍 1, 2, 3, 4 or 5? #archoskar
.
"The pursuit, even of the best things, ought to be calm and tranquil." — Marcus Tullius Cicero. #architectureoskar
.
1: The 'Olive Mill'.
Designed by Berrow (@berrowprojects).
Located in Sóller, Mallorca, Spain.
Visualized by BergaGonzález (@bergagonzalez).
.
2: The 'Luxury Pool'.
Designed & visualized by NORTHSTONE (@thenorthstonegroup) from Montreal, Quebec, Canada.
.
3: The 'BIANCO' (211 m²).
Designed by Stanislav Ananev, Vorobyeva Tanya & Lidia Ivanova (@ananevdesign, @vorobyeva_tanya_v & @lidiamidia, 2021).
Inspired by the location of Yekaterinburg, Russia.
Visualized by Dmitry Gubarev (@gubarev_dmitry).
.
4: The 'Chaká House⁣' (333 m²).
Designed by QuesnelArqs (@quesnelarqs⁣, 2014).
Located in Mérida, Yucatán, Mexico.
Photo by Manolo R Solis (@manolorsolis_fotografia⁣).
.
5: The 'Pier'.
Designed & visualized by Paul Milinski (@paul_milinski, 2020) from Melbourne, Australia.
.
#pickoftheday #pick #patio #calm

node.text:
Tropical forest hotel 💚 #archoskar
The 'Botanique Hotel & Spa' (7000 m²).
Designed by Candida Tabet Arquitetura (@candidatabet, 2006).
Located in São Carlos, Brazil.
Photos by Tuca Reinés (@tucareines).
Description by Candida Tabet Arquitetura.
.
"One sees great things from the valley; only small things from the peak." — Gilbert K. Chesterton. #architectureoskar
.
Nestled in a confluence of three rich river valleys, amid picturesque hillsides and stunning ridges in the heart of the Mantiqueira Mountains, south-east of Brazil, 'Botanique Hotel & Spa' is enveloped and surrounded by lush, mid-tropical Atlantic forests, 1200m above sea level.
.
#tropical #forest #hotel #brazil

node.text:
Organic architecture hidden beneath green dunes 💚 #archoskar
The 'Casa Organica' (178 m²).
Designed by Javier Senosiain (@javiersenosiaina, 1984).
Located in Naucalpan de Juárez, Mexico.
Video by Brenda Coto (@brendacoto).
Song by Lil Peep, 'Star Shopping'.
.
"Organic architecture seeks superior sense of use and a finer sense of comfort, expressed in organic simplicity." — Frank Lloyd Wright. #architectureoskar
.
The original idea of the project took its simile from a peanut shell: two wide oval spaces with lots of light, united by a space in low and narrow gloom. 'Organic House' is defined in two large spaces: one day and one night, with interior based on the elementary functions of man. The design seeks to show its uniqueness without losing the integration of the exterior green areas.
.
#organic #peanut #mexico #franklloydwright

node.text:
Pick your favourite Pool 😍 1, 2, 3, 4 or 5? #archoskar
.
"Water, taken in moderation, cannot hurt anybody." — Mark Twain. #architectureoskar
.
1: The 'House in Afife'.
Designed by Guilherme Machado Vaz (@guilhermachadovaz, 2018).
Located in Afife, Viana Do Castelo, Portugal.
Photo by Jose Campos (@josecamposphotographer).
.
2: The 'Wall House' (1100 m²).
Designed by José Guedes Cruz, César Marques & Marco Marinho (Guedes Cruz Arquitectos, @guedescruzarquitectos).
Located in Cascais, Lisbon, Portugal.
Photo by Ricardo Oliveira Alves (@ricardoliveiralves).
.
3: The 'Neuendorf House' (@neuendorfhouse).
Designed by Claudio Silvestrin & John Pawson (1987-1989).
Located in Mallorca, Spain.
Photo by Jelena (@jelena.marija).
.
4: The 'Oak Pass Residence' (492 m²).
Designed by SIMO design (@simo_design, 2019).
Located in Beverly Hills, California, USA.
Photo by Alex Zarour (@virtuallyherestudios).
.
5: The 'Splitwater'.
Designed & visualised by Andrea Bertaccini (2011) from Forlì, Italy.
.
#pickoftheday #pick #pool #marktwain
